25|$|In 1911 the <b>Theosophical</b> <b>Society</b> {{established}} the Order of the Star in the East (OSE) {{to prepare the}} world for the expected appearance of the World Teacher. Krishnamurti was named as its head, with senior Theosophists assigned various other positions. Membership was open to anybody who accepted the doctrine of the Coming of the World Teacher. Controversy soon erupted, both within the <b>Theosophical</b> <b>Society</b> and outside it, in Hindu circles and the Indian press.|$|E
